cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses model-driven development (MDD) and proposes a method for reducing the cost, increasing the quality, and broadening the applicability of MDD systems by embedding modeling languages within established formal languages and using analyzers for synthesis purposes. This work focuses on partial specifications of particular aspects of the system, such as application architectures and target platforms, and synthesizing partial code bases from such specifications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of formal languages and analyzers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses synthesizing object-relational mapping tradeoff spaces and database schemas, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
